件号:
NAS1399D4-3铆钉/托板BACN10JR6CFD已加
按如下临时处理，航材已加。
1. Remove the damaged nutplate.

2. Perform a detailed visual inspection (DVI) at x10 magnification of the discrepant area to ensure there is no additional damage.

3. Perform HFEC inspection of the rivet holes per 737 NDT Manual Part 6, 51-00-00, Procedure 16 to verify a crack-free condition. Ensure the diameters of the rivet holes are within DWG tolerance.

4. There is no damage per Steps 2 and 3.

5. Apply a chemical conversion coating to bare aluminum surfaces per SOPM 20-43-03.

6. Install the BACN10JR6CFD nutplate with NAS1399D4* blind rivets per SRM 51-40-02.

7. After nutplate installation, install 315A2258 de-activation pin or equivalent tooling pin to align floating nut with bushings. Seal floating nut to base using BMS5-26 per BAC5000 fillet seal requirements. Leave pin installed until sufficient curing of sealant has occurred to retain aligned position. Nut movement shall be limited by cured sealant. Sealant not allowed in hole or threads of nutplate or hole of fitting detail.

8. Replace the installed blind rivets with BACR15GF4D* solid rivets at next C Check or 24 months, whichever comes first.
